snippet: Liz Cheney, the oldest daughter of former Vice President Dick Cheney, has made it clear that she wants to run for the United States Senate seat now held by Michael B. Enzi, a fellow Republican.
abstract: Liz Cheney, oldest daughter of former Vice Pres Dick Cheney, has made it clear that she wants to run for Senate seat held by Michael B Enzi, incumbent Wyoming Republican; Cheney's ambitions threaten to start civil war within state's Republican establishment, and reflect greater tension within party as younger generation feels less reluctance to challenge incumbents, especially if they are seen as too consensus-minded or insufficiently conservative.
lead_paragraph: Liz Cheney, the oldest daughter of former Vice President Dick Cheney, has made it clear that she wants to run for the United States Senate seat now held by Michael B. Enzi, a fellow Republican.

headline.main: In Wyoming, a Cheney Run Worries G.O.P.
headline.print_headline: In Wyoming, A Cheney Run Worries G.O.P.
